==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[#Latin|Alcyone]], from Greek [[Ἀλκυων]] (''Alkyon'')
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Alcyone'''

#{{greekmyth}}: One of the [[Pleides]]; daughter of [[Aeolus]] and wife of [[Ceyx]]. When her husband dies in a [[shipwreck]], Alcyone threw herself into the sea whereupon the gods thransformed both into [[halcyon]] birds (kingfishers).   When Alcyone made her nest on the [[beach]], [[wave]]s threatened to destroy it. Aeolus restrained his winds and made the waves be calm during seven days in each year, so she could lay her eggs. These became known as the "halcyon days", when storms never occur.

